stories.text: Reading Brad Feld's "Startup Boards", which I am guessing most have read on HN.  Noticed it was written or last updated in 2014.  That's getting a bit long in the tooth.  I assume much of the content is still applicable, but wondering if some takeaways have changed?
stories.title: Startup Boards by Brad Feld – Has much changed since 2014?

stories.text:
Wondering if anyone has tried a service like Nebula.org that claims to offer 100% genome sequencing and reports?

Did you find it to be more insightful than partial sequencing like 23&Me? What did you learn?
stories.title: Ask HN: Has anyone tried whole genome sequencing?
